cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses a system that discovers Internet address structure based on analyses of a subset of IPv6 addresses known to be active, which is relevant to network security. It could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with IPv6 addresses and their structure. Additionally, the paper employs machine learning techniques, which could place it in the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper presents results based on probabilistic modeling, which could also place it in the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
